The paper deals with the problem of ranking items using adaptive elicitation of subset-wise preference feedback, which is a problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of Plackett-Luce models, which are commonly used in statistics and probability theory, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper involves the use of sample complexity analysis, which is a topic in information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category.
